[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
pass 1NT pass 4NT pass 6NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: N, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 2, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "2978084c8bab0c6c65268af85f61db85e47da46ec5dd3924182b01ff953f22ea"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/blackwood"]
[Student "S"]
{You have a textbook 1NT opener, so you open 1NT. Partner says 4NT.  

<b>THIS IS NOT BLACKWOOD</b>. Partner's bid is the Quantitative 4NT. He has 16 points and is inviting you to bid slam if you have a maximum opener, but to pass with a minimum. Since your 17 point hand is at the top of the 1NT range you accept the invitation and bid 6NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:964.AJ953.AQJ3.7 T72.T.T9854.8642 KQJ83.K8764.7.AK A5.Q2.K62.QJT953"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "6H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1H pass 4NT pass 5H pass 6H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "1678be9e527d4ba976e187056194fe953390cc3c54f176d327ea61d4109e0f1f"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/blackwood"]
[Student "S"]
{You <b>COULD</b> make a Splinter Bid with this hand. You have a singleton \D and great trump support. However it is usually not worthwhile Splintering when you have the strong hand that will be taking control. Since what you really want to know is how many Aces partner has you just ask him with a 4NT bid. Partner answers 5\H.  

Missing one Ace you bid 6\H.}

